>JS required
Come on.
What do you guys think of starting a simple static html-only website over ipfs sharing the manifestos and videos of these shooters?
I'm thinking of something really simple that'll avoid splitting the seeder base by not distributing the actual content over ipfs (which is not currently usable for large files due to being user-unfriendly anyway), and sticking to whatever was the first/most popular torrent to pop up if any. The torrent will be a magnet link, no .torrent files, because magnets can be built into the website's html and are reachable so long as a peer has the metadata, while a .torrent file is a fracture point
For instance doorcuck made a torrent with his shit, we'd use that torrent. Kiwifarms made a torrent of his stream and everyone is using it, so we use that torrent.  Tarrant's stream has a kiwifarms torrent, we'd link that. Tarrant's manifesto that I've seen has only been shared through filehost links, so we'd make a torrent of that.
You lied to /b/. How could you?
